String is a class in java 

String a ="nitin"            // here a is reference variable and "nitin" is object 

string b="nitin"             // here string a and b both pointing to same object which creates different memory string pool in heap memory


// now if we want to create 2 differnet objects then 


String a= new String ("nitin");
String b=new String ("nitin");           // now these are stored in 2 different memories
